article.description: Bryant Horn threw for 158 yards and a score and rushed 11 times for 73 yards and two touchdowns and Jacksonville State rolled past Eastern Kentucky 41-25 on Saturday.
article.headline: Jacksonville St. rolls to 41-25 win over E. Kentucky
article.linkText: Jacksonville St. rolls to 41-25 win over E. Kentucky
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- Bryant Horn threw for 158 yards and a score and rushed 11 times for 73 yards and two touchdowns and Jacksonville State rolled past Eastern Kentucky 41-25 on Saturday. De'Marcus Flowers took the opening kickoff and returned it 66 yards to the Eastern Kentucky 33-yard line. Horn then ended the short drive with a 13-yard touchdown run and a lead that was never challenged. Eastern Kentucky took its opening possession and went on a 15-play march that ended, when on third-and-goal at the Gamecocks' 13, Siran Neal picked off Tim Boyle in the end zone for a touchback. Jacksonville State's Roc Thomas finished a 6-play, 80-yard drive with a 12-yard touchdown run. Cade Stinnet's 46-yard field goal midway through the third quarter made the score 34-3. Jacksonville State (5-1, 3-0 Ohio Valley) now has won a record 27 straight games in conference play. Boyle threw for 186 yards and a touchdown with two interceptions for Eastern Kentucky (1-5, 1-3). --- More AP college football: http://collegefootball.ap.org and http://www.twitter.com/AP-Top25
